> > 13. BUILD uses the "unformed" list, so one can predict structure ID's.
> >     May specify as a fourth argument to BUILD, as in G1 with FORM.
> 

> While being able to build a
> tower to avoid attack is not a great game mechanic, most players are
> not smart enough to issue 100,000 orders. You might want to add
> "castle" "tower" "inn" as an alias to the first such structure in a
> province. Then the rules weirdness is someone who builds 2 towers and
> hides in the second.
> 
> ======================================================================
> 
> I think G2 will fail to be "open ended" if you don't stop noble point
> transfers.  One easy to do that would be to charge players NPs for any
> NPs they acquire through terrorize/persuade/potion etc. Any faction
> with a negative NP balance will sort-of lose their new "free" NPs and
> if they have bodies decay, those NPs won't be available to form new
> characters.
> 
> Example: I have 1 NP, and I eat BtA's brain, which gives me skills
> worth 6 NP's. My NP balance is now -5 NPs. I can't form a new
> character until I raise my NP balance to be positive, via waiting or
> having bodies decay.
> 
> I suppose you should also have decaying bodies yield up all of their
> NPs instead of just 1. I think this is a good way of keeping defeated
> players in the game, actually. Having an experienced character lose
> his study time is a huge penalty for losing a noble...
> 
> ======================================================================
> 


> 4) Aura blasted characters should not die until the end of the
> month. Remember that I was complaining that it was too complex to
> write movement orders which took care of your stack leader being aura
> blasted? I'm not sure if this rule is necessary but it would make the
> game better. Of course the same would have to apply to lightning bolts
> and other magical ways of killing nobles. The "fog of death" against
> armies will never get used when you could kill the stack leader
> instead...



